  "description": "Seasons change, your training doesn\u2019t have to. Paired with a training app, you can ride with friends all over the world. Powerful electromagnetic resistance adjusts automatically for the course you're riding. Or you can just hop on for a training ride without an app controlling the resistance. The M2 delivers the same smooth power curve as Saris\u2019 Fluid2 trainer.Electromagnetic resistance is responsive and quiet, only 69dB at 32Km/h.Power accuracy readings +/-5%.Integrated sensors for speed, cadence and power.Works with Zwift\u2122, Rouvy\u2122, TrainerRoad\u2122 and more.Communicates over ANT+ FE-C and Bluetooth to connect to devices and sensors.Simulates grades up to 15%Internal cooling system keeps air moving through the trainer, so temperatures stay reasonable.Maximum rider and bike weight of 136kg.Broad frame design stays stable in the sprints.Folds for storage (56 x 23 x 51cm).Tool-free mounting and roller adjustment.5cm resistance unit roller allows for the following wheel sizes 650b, 700c, 27.5in. \u2013 up to a 2.0in. tire and 29in. \u2013 up to a 1.5in. (not including tread).Fits road and mountain bike frames, includes steel quick-release skewer with rear dropout spacing: 120mm, 130mm and 135mm.LED indicators signal connections to devices and sensors.Precision machined roller reduces tire-wear.Adjustable feet keep it level.Includes free 1 month subscription to Rouvy\u2019s virtual training app.",
